  <p>Napa Valley wines display remarkable visual diversity. <strong>Cabernet Sauvignon</strong> typically exhibits deep garnet to inky purple hues, with younger wines showing vibrant violet edges that evolve to brick-red meniscus with age. The wine's viscosity creates pronounced "legs" on the glass, indicating the region's characteristic high alcohol content (14.5-16%) and glycerol from concentrated fruit. <strong>Chardonnay</strong> ranges from pale straw with green highlights in cool-climate expressions to rich golden amber in barrel-fermented examples from warmer appellations like Rutherford.</p>
